An exception that Athena received when it called a custom metastore. Occurs if the error is not caused by user input (InvalidRequestException) or from the Athena platform (InternalServerException). For example, if a user-created Lambda function is missing permissions, the Lambda 4XX exception is returned in a MetadataException.
Indicates a platform issue, which may be due to a transient condition or outage.

Amazon Athena is an interactive query service that lets you use standard SQL to analyze data directly in Amazon S3. You can point Athena at your data in Amazon S3 and run ad-hoc queries and get results in seconds. Athena is serverless, so there is no infrastructure to set up or manage. You pay only for the queries you run. Athena scales automatically—executing queries in parallel—so results are fast, even with large datasets and complex queries. For more information, see

in the Amazon Athena User Guide. If you connect to Athena using the JDBC driver, use version 1.1.0 of the driver or later with the Amazon Athena API. Earlier version drivers do not support the API. For more information and to download the driver, see
